The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) campaign spokesman in Kaduna has been arrested following a viral video in which he was seen inciting violence
Ben Bako was arrested on Saturday by security operatives in Kaduna around 11 p.m.
He has been flown to Abuja by security agents believed to be from the State Security Service (SSS) â€Ž.


Confirming the arrest, the deputy director of publicity of the PDP campaign, Yakubu Lere, said Mr Bako was taken by the SSS to Abuja.


The party has yet to make its position public.
